03:54.854 --> 03:56.890
(Singing continues quietly)

03:56.924 --> 04:00.927
(Footsteps sloshing)

04:00.962 --> 04:04.330
- (Gasps)
- (Blade slicing)

04:11.907 --> 04:14.076
(Groans)

04:29.787 --> 04:31.453
(Gurgling)

04:35.393 --> 04:38.529
(Singing continues)

04:48.578 --> 04:50.279
Welsh!

04:52.383 --> 04:54.620
Oi, Welsh!

04:54.654 --> 04:56.623
Are you done yet?

05:14.538 --> 05:17.106
(Slices)

05:23.608 --> 05:25.508
The damn fool makes for the trees

05:25.542 --> 05:27.343
when I've told him a hundred times,

05:27.377 --> 05:29.812
you start on the outside
and work your way in.

05:29.846 --> 05:32.480
He's a greenhorn, huh?

05:41.988 --> 05:45.755
(Imitates birdcall)

05:51.961 --> 05:54.364
- Ah!
- (Grunts)

05:54.398 --> 05:56.401
MAN: Come on, lads!
Let's run him, boys!

05:56.435 --> 05:59.237
Let's run him like a dog!

06:02.513 --> 06:04.783
- Come on, lads!
- (Shouting)

06:04.817 --> 06:07.119
(Gunfire)

06:14.595 --> 06:17.662
SOLDIER: They were waiting for us.
They knew where we would be.

06:17.696 --> 06:20.668
- MAN: They couldn't have known.
- They were waiting.

06:23.905 --> 06:25.271
How?

06:25.305 --> 06:29.108
These were not
Tory militia or Regulars.

06:29.143 --> 06:33.378
They... they were Queen's Rangers.

06:42.891 --> 06:45.126
Was it Robert Rogers?

06:48.765 --> 06:50.231
It was luck, then.

06:50.266 --> 06:53.400
Just bad luck you ran into him.

06:53.434 --> 06:54.903
I asked for a coat.

06:54.937 --> 06:56.405
Luck?

06:56.440 --> 06:59.343
Sir, luck had nothing to do with this.

06:59.377 --> 07:01.177
We both know that. The...

07:02.978 --> 07:06.751
The British, they use Rogers and
his mercenaries like a bear trap,

07:06.785 --> 07:08.918
and they knew precisely
where to set him.

07:08.952 --> 07:11.421
This was an ambush planned in advance.

07:11.456 --> 07:14.460
Are you saying there's a
breach within our ranks?

07:27.501 --> 07:29.599
I'm saying

07:29.634 --> 07:33.170
that they have spies everywhere, sir...

07:34.339 --> 07:37.273
and that we need the same.

07:37.307 --> 07:39.274
See to your shoulder.

07:39.309 --> 07:41.476
After you've recovered,
I'll assign you new men.

07:41.510 --> 07:44.845
General, please.
These scouting runs, they're suicide.

07:44.880 --> 07:47.115
We have discussed this,
Captain Tallmadge.

07:47.149 --> 07:50.017
I will not waste money on informers.

07:50.052 --> 07:52.487
I agree, sir.
All I would need from you

07:52.521 --> 07:57.288
is one man to serve as a courier
between myself and a friend in New York.

07:57.322 --> 08:00.392
- If we can establish...
- New York?

08:00.426 --> 08:03.229
After Washington has burned it
to the ground upon our retreat?

08:04.131 --> 08:05.498
Benjamin...

08:07.366 --> 08:10.165
we have no friends in New York.

08:14.502 --> 08:17.237
