08:17.271 --> 08:19.572
<i>â™ª There's snakes in the garden... â™ª</i>

08:19.607 --> 08:22.776
<i>â™ª Soul for sale... â™ª</i>

08:22.811 --> 08:25.650
<i>â™ª Blood on the rise â™ª</i>

08:26.753 --> 08:28.958
<i>â™ª Hush, hush â™ª</i>

08:28.992 --> 08:33.429
<i>- â™ª I can't wait anymore â™ª
- â™ª Soul for sale... â™ª</i>

08:35.030 --> 08:38.770
<i>â™ª I can't wait anymore â™ª</i>

08:41.039 --> 08:44.106
<i>â™ª Hush, hush â™ª</i>

08:46.678 --> 08:49.010
(Birds chirping)

08:57.968 --> 08:59.786
It's bad.

09:21.000 --> 09:22.933
(Grunts)

09:24.769 --> 09:27.005
- (Soldiers chatting)
- (Horse whinnies)

09:47.159 --> 09:49.828
(Clicks tongue)
Come on.

09:49.863 --> 09:52.129
(Clicks tongue)
Come on, hup.

10:12.405 --> 10:14.373
(Bleating)

10:18.243 --> 10:21.044
(Men cheering, laughing)

10:27.047 --> 10:29.017
(Coins jingle)

10:30.836 --> 10:34.510
Mr. Strong! Four ales, please!

10:49.236 --> 10:53.141
- Good evening, Selah.
- Thought you didn't like my tavern.

11:00.316 --> 11:03.581
- What's this?
- I said I would repay my debt.

11:04.086 --> 11:06.955
We're not even halfway
through the season.

11:06.989 --> 11:09.124
This is only half of what I owe.

11:10.959 --> 11:14.261
- The harvest isn't coming in as I hoped.
- Loopers or maggots?

11:14.296 --> 11:16.162
I just need more time, Selah,
and then next season, I swear...

11:16.196 --> 11:19.301
Next season? Of course, why not?

11:19.335 --> 11:24.307
Perhaps by then you just pay me
back with my own cauliflower.

11:27.315 --> 11:28.949
Abraham.

11:36.256 --> 11:38.590
To what do we owe the pleasure?

11:38.625 --> 11:41.960
Abe and I were
just discussing maggots.

11:41.994 --> 11:43.461
Maggots?

11:43.496 --> 11:45.798
Mrs. Strong, here, here!

11:48.469 --> 11:51.971
I hear they've been dethroned
as Setauket's reigning pests.

11:52.006 --> 11:55.341
- Ahem.
- Your rooms are ready, gentlemen.

11:55.375 --> 11:57.942
Well, I should be off, so...

11:57.976 --> 11:59.810
No, now, wait.

11:59.844 --> 12:02.179
We hardly see you anymore.

12:03.114 --> 12:06.485
How is Mary and Thomas?

12:06.520 --> 12:08.220
They're both well.

12:09.656 --> 12:12.359
- I really should...
- You should come for dinner

12:12.393 --> 12:14.260
at our house. The three of you.

12:14.295 --> 12:17.797
- SELAH: Anna.
- I fear that wouldn't feel right.

12:21.000 --> 12:24.100
I owe your husband a debt.

12:24.135 --> 12:27.501
I would be shamed for you to cook
for us while I'm in arrears.

12:28.435 --> 12:30.369
I didn't know about this.

12:31.404 --> 12:34.472
Bloody news! Bloody news!

12:34.507 --> 12:37.573
"Where are the rebels now?"

12:37.608 --> 12:40.777
To the brave Patriot commander

12:40.812 --> 12:43.481
on the eve of his retreat...

12:43.515 --> 12:47.218
"Pardon, his charge
into northern New Jersey."

12:47.252 --> 12:48.820
(Soldiers laughing)

12:48.855 --> 12:51.791
"Pulled back from the line,
a most propitious sign,

12:51.825 --> 12:54.395
for Mrs. Washington, that sow."

12:54.429 --> 12:57.699
(Laughing)

12:57.733 --> 13:00.770
"Alas, before his return,
dear Georgie must discern

13:00.804 --> 13:03.806
in what place he should
sheathe his saber."

13:03.840 --> 13:05.274
(Laughing continues)

13:05.309 --> 13:07.644
- SOLDIER: "But surely..."
- Go upstairs.

13:07.678 --> 13:09.130
Selah, don't.

13:09.208 --> 13:11.806
"...the joke of it all
is that his scabbard calls

13:11.883 --> 13:15.087
for any puff's sword he can stow."

13:15.121 --> 13:19.259
(Laughing, pounding)

13:21.663 --> 13:23.231
Get out, Robeson.

13:24.500 --> 13:26.464
I'm sorry, did I offend

13:26.499 --> 13:28.766
your sensitive liberal puff cake?

13:28.801 --> 13:30.969
You offended my wife.
Now, leave.

13:31.003 --> 13:34.139
MAN:
Come off it, man.

13:34.173 --> 13:37.709
We're celebrating your
king's victory in New York.

13:37.743 --> 13:39.578
ROBESON: Though we understand
how that might upset

13:39.612 --> 13:42.112
a certain delegate
to the Provincial Congress.

13:42.146 --> 13:43.979
- Drunk.
- Whig.

13:50.116 --> 13:52.984
- You stupid...
- Anna, don't, don't, don't.

13:53.019 --> 13:55.053
(Glass shatters)

13:55.087 --> 13:56.322
(Groans)

13:56.356 --> 13:58.760
SOLDIER:
Did he just hit Captain Joyce?

14:01.229 --> 14:03.330
(Glasses shatter)

14:05.002 --> 14:07.272
(Groans)

14:08.641 --> 14:10.242
Let me help you.
Let me get that for you.

14:10.275 --> 14:12.655
- Out of my way.
- Here, it's fine.

14:12.690 --> 14:14.917
Take your coat off.
There you are, just...

14:14.952 --> 14:17.223
- (Fabric rips)
- Ah!

14:17.257 --> 14:19.658
Release the captain, please.

14:22.832 --> 14:24.600
Of course.

14:24.634 --> 14:26.202
(Groans)

14:27.904 --> 14:30.642
(Coughs)

14:34.445 --> 14:36.646
(Glass shattering)

14:39.518 --> 14:41.620
(Sawing)

14:45.821 --> 14:48.989
Leave room for two nooses.

14:51.492 --> 14:53.269
JOYCE:
Court-martialed?

14:53.931 --> 14:56.897
Major, please. Show mercy.

14:57.022 --> 14:59.400
Law, order,

14:59.734 --> 15:02.103
authority.

15:02.137 --> 15:03.839
We are the beacon of authority

15:03.874 --> 15:05.341
in these colonies, Captain,

15:05.375 --> 15:08.208
and we bear the burden
of that authority.

15:08.243 --> 15:10.143
Major...

15:10.177 --> 15:13.579
"Because authority,
though it err like others,"

15:13.613 --> 15:17.082
hath yet a kind of medicine in itself

15:17.116 --> 15:20.352
"that skins the vice o' the top."

15:20.387 --> 15:23.187
- Do you understand?
- Is the major in?

15:23.222 --> 15:25.009
Wait here.

15:25.190 --> 15:27.860
Sir, this colonist has struck

15:27.894 --> 15:30.394
an officer of His Majesty's
Royal Army.

15:30.428 --> 15:32.196
Now, once I testify...

15:32.230 --> 15:34.832
- You will not be court-martialed here.
- Oh.

15:34.867 --> 15:37.437
You will return to England,

15:37.471 --> 15:41.141
where you'll be cashiered
directly upon arrival.

15:41.175 --> 15:42.609
Dismissed.

16:03.867 --> 16:06.035
I knew that you would come.

16:06.069 --> 16:08.971
I wish to offer my services,
for whatever they may be worth.

16:09.005 --> 16:12.243
Mm, this is not a matter
for the provincial court.

16:12.277 --> 16:15.483
One of my men was assaulted.

16:15.517 --> 16:17.551
- This must be redressed.
- Without question.

16:17.585 --> 16:19.453
But by the looks
of Captain Joyce just now,

16:19.487 --> 16:21.087
I can tell there's more to this story,

16:21.121 --> 16:23.926
and I thought I would
shed light on a few facts

16:23.961 --> 16:25.895
in the service of clarity.

16:25.929 --> 16:29.331
It involves some social
history of Setauket.

16:29.365 --> 16:31.300
Provincial ephemera

16:31.334 --> 16:33.336
and the passions of young people.

16:33.370 --> 16:34.504
Probably worthless.

16:34.538 --> 16:38.241
(Blows)
What history?

16:40.083 --> 16:44.282
Anna Strong,
the wife of Selah Strong,

16:44.316 --> 16:48.919
was engaged three years ago
to Abraham Woodhull.

16:48.953 --> 16:50.686
You mean Abraham, your son.

16:50.721 --> 16:53.026
Yes, they were childhood
friends, you see,

16:53.060 --> 16:55.397
and our families shared friendship

16:55.431 --> 16:59.799
until her father's patriot
politics drove us to disagreement.

16:59.834 --> 17:03.806
Anna, unfortunately, took
her father's views to heart

17:03.840 --> 17:07.174
and so broke the heart of my son,

17:07.209 --> 17:09.477
who was raised to love
the law above all else.

17:11.680 --> 17:15.114
"Love will not be spurred
to what it loathes."

17:15.483 --> 17:18.663
So, why, then, did he rush
to the aid of her husband,

17:18.686 --> 17:21.790
a suspected patriot?

17:21.824 --> 17:25.060
Abraham has a dreamer's heart,

17:25.095 --> 17:27.097
a romantic heart,

17:27.132 --> 17:30.299
his mother's heart, if truth be told.

17:30.333 --> 17:33.137
And he keeps room there for Anna

17:33.171 --> 17:35.005
in spite of her betrayal.

17:35.039 --> 17:37.540
Mm.

17:37.574 --> 17:39.842
"Alas, that love,

17:39.876 --> 17:42.612
so gentle in his view..."

17:42.646 --> 17:46.818
BOTH: "...should be so
tyrannous and rough in proof."

17:54.726 --> 17:57.095
(Panting)

18:00.938 --> 18:02.771
Evening, Woodhull.

18:02.805 --> 18:04.239
What are you doing?

18:04.273 --> 18:06.510
(Slices rope)

18:07.446 --> 18:09.146
Where are you taking Selah?

18:09.181 --> 18:12.614
It's past curfew.
Run home to your father.

18:16.016 --> 18:19.852
(Thunder crashing)

18:37.959 --> 18:39.661
(Door opens)

18:39.696 --> 18:42.196
(Panting)

18:42.230 --> 18:44.065
(Door closes)

18:46.801 --> 18:48.968
- Let me see you.
- I'm fine.

18:49.003 --> 18:50.403
Just a few bumps, that's all.

18:50.437 --> 18:52.304
(Winces)
Ah, ah.

18:52.338 --> 18:54.973
How did this happen?
Why would you even go to that place?

18:55.008 --> 18:56.909
Mary, Mary.

18:56.944 --> 18:59.881
I'm fine. I'm home.

19:01.582 --> 19:03.450
I went down the tavern
for a drink, is all.

19:03.485 --> 19:06.722
Lord knows I could do with another one.
(Winces)

19:06.757 --> 19:09.290
- Eat something first.
- Yeah, yeah.

19:22.704 --> 19:24.802
(Groans)

19:29.811 --> 19:31.380
Is that one of mine?

19:31.415 --> 19:33.082
They were your brother's
before they were yours.

19:33.117 --> 19:34.784
I thought you wouldn't mind
if I brought one

19:34.819 --> 19:37.187
for my little soldier here.

19:37.221 --> 19:39.430
I don't know what
Major Hewlett told you

19:39.596 --> 19:42.393
or what was said to him, but the
fault with this lies with...

19:42.428 --> 19:45.127
- Selah Strong.
- With John Robeson.

19:45.161 --> 19:48.093
He was the one
who started the fight.

19:48.128 --> 19:50.860
And Captain Joyce,
who was well into his cup,

19:50.894 --> 19:52.798
slipped and cut his hand
on one. That is all.

19:52.832 --> 19:54.267
I doubt that's how he'll testify,

19:54.302 --> 19:56.770
so be glad that testimony
won't name you.

19:59.006 --> 20:00.406
Abraham...

20:02.109 --> 20:04.343
why did you take money
from that man?

20:05.680 --> 20:07.653
I warned you about Selah Strong.

20:07.778 --> 20:11.515
- He's choleric by nature.
- (Thomas crying)

20:11.550 --> 20:14.752
You should've come to me if
you needed specie or credit.

20:14.787 --> 20:16.385
I have contacts on New York Island

20:16.419 --> 20:18.384
who'd buy my hogs
at twice the market value.

20:18.418 --> 20:21.052
All I need is someone
to run them into the city.

20:21.086 --> 20:23.692
Sprout, let me give you
a little piece of advice

20:23.726 --> 20:26.463
that my father here gave to me once.

20:26.497 --> 20:28.898
"Neither a lender nor a borrower be."

20:28.932 --> 20:30.266
You wouldn't have borrowed.
You would have worked.

20:30.300 --> 20:32.267
(Thomas crying)

20:35.068 --> 20:37.238
Good boy. Shh.

20:37.272 --> 20:38.840
Good boy.

20:38.874 --> 20:40.441
Good night.

20:47.682 --> 20:49.251
(Sighs)

20:49.285 --> 20:51.487
(Winces)
Let's have it.

21:02.671 --> 21:04.737
I'll speak plain now.

21:06.339 --> 21:09.407
You have responsibilities
to more than this farm,

21:09.441 --> 21:11.007
to more than yourself.

21:11.042 --> 21:14.944
- But, Father, I...
- Legacy is everything.

21:14.978 --> 21:19.282
If you wish to preserve ours,
then stay away from those

21:19.316 --> 21:22.186
who've already chosen
to sully theirs.

21:22.221 --> 21:25.888
The Smiths, the Strongs,
the Tallmadges...

21:25.923 --> 21:28.024
they chose the wrong side.

21:29.060 --> 21:30.561
I wasn't taking sides.

21:34.131 --> 21:36.830
I was just trying to do right.

21:36.865 --> 21:39.701
Try harder.

21:41.705 --> 21:43.370
And think on my offer.

21:44.706 --> 21:46.642
Good night.

21:49.879 --> 21:53.680
(Door opens, closes)

21:54.848 --> 21:58.250
(Rain pattering)

22:03.386 --> 22:05.719
(Shivering)

22:05.753 --> 22:07.386
- Who's that? Who's there?
- It's me, it's me.

22:07.420 --> 22:10.021
What are you doing?
There's a sentry.

22:10.056 --> 22:12.256
He's staying dry for now.

22:12.291 --> 22:14.893
We don't have much time,
all right, so please listen well.

22:14.927 --> 22:17.462
They are planning to charge
you with insurrection.

22:17.496 --> 22:19.399
I struck a redcoat,
that's all that matters.

22:19.433 --> 22:21.734
No, no, not if you plead
guilty to the first charge.

22:21.768 --> 22:24.169
Look, everyone knows
that Joyce is a drunkard.

22:24.203 --> 22:27.872
They don't want to hang anyone in
Setauket, not in secure territory.

22:27.906 --> 22:31.644
They're gonna send you
instead to the Jersey.

22:31.678 --> 22:34.412
- Prison ship?
- Where you have friends.

22:34.446 --> 22:36.946
You know others who have gone
and others who have gotten out.

22:36.981 --> 22:39.299
- If you bribe someone...
- Is that why you came here?

22:39.376 --> 22:41.372
To tell me this?

22:41.623 --> 22:43.223
No, I came here to warn you.

22:43.257 --> 22:45.591
And to have me forgive
your debt, no doubt.

22:45.625 --> 22:47.427
No, I said I'd repay my debt in full.

22:47.461 --> 22:49.331
I promised you that.

22:51.267 --> 22:53.867
I'll make you a new deal.

22:53.902 --> 22:55.635
What?

22:58.575 --> 23:00.675
Take care of her for me.

23:07.148 --> 23:10.752
She'll be all alone to run
our house and the tavern.

23:14.857 --> 23:18.491
You take care of Anna while I'm gone

23:18.526 --> 23:20.695
and I will forgive you your debt.

23:20.729 --> 23:23.032
I don't need your forgiveness.

23:27.106 --> 23:29.838
You are her husband, Selah.

23:31.508 --> 23:34.375
And I'm going to repay my debt.

